#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn9.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga "
msgstr "1. In the Woods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Anuruddhasutta "
msgstr "6. With Anuruddha "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn9.6:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā anuruddho kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Anuruddha was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.6:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho aññatarā tāvatiṃsakāyikā devatā jālinī nāma āyasmato anuruddhassa purāṇadutiyikā yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then a certain deity of the company of the Thirty-Three named Penelope had been Anuruddha’s partner in a former life. She went up to Anuruddha, and recited these verses: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.431, sc2
msgctxt "sn9.6:2.1"
msgid "“Tattha cittaṃ paṇidhehi, "
msgstr "“Set your heart there, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:2.2"
msgid "yattha te vusitaṃ pure; "
msgstr "where you used to live; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:2.3"
msgid "Tāvatiṃsesu devesu, "
msgstr "among the gods of the Thirty-Three, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:2.4"
msgid "sabbakāmasamiddhisu; "
msgstr "whose every desire is granted! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:2.5"
msgid "Purakkhato parivuto, "
msgstr "At the fore of a retinue "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:2.6"
msgid "devakaññāhi sobhasī”ti. "
msgstr "of divine maidens, you’ll shine!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn9.6:3.1"
msgid "“Duggatā devakaññāyo, "
msgstr "“Divine maidens are in a sorry state, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:3.2"
msgid "sakkāyasmiṃ patiṭṭhitā; "
msgstr "stuck in self-identity. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:3.3"
msgid "Te cāpi duggatā sattā, "
msgstr "And those beings too are in a sorry state, "

# NOTE: See BB for reading.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:3.4"
msgid "devakaññāhi patthitā”ti. "
msgstr "who are attached to divine maidens.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn9.6:4.1"
msgid "“Na te sukhaṃ pajānanti, "
msgstr "“They don’t know pleasure "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:4.2"
msgid "ye na passanti nandanaṃ; "
msgstr "who don’t see the Garden of Delight! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:4.3"
msgid "Āvāsaṃ naradevānaṃ, "
msgstr "It’s the abode of lordly gods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:4.4"
msgid "tidasānaṃ yasassinan”ti. "
msgstr "the glorious host of Thirty!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn9.6:5.1"
msgid "“Na tvaṃ bāle vijānāsi, "
msgstr "“Fool, don’t you understand "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:5.2"
msgid "yathā arahataṃ vaco; "
msgstr "the saying of the perfected ones: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:5.3"
msgid "Aniccā sabbasaṅkhārā, "
msgstr "all conditions are impermanent, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:5.4"
msgid "uppādavayadhammino; "
msgstr "their nature is to rise and fall; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:5.5"
msgid "Uppajjitvā nirujjhanti, "
msgstr "having arisen, they cease; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:5.6"
msgid "tesaṃ vūpasamo sukho. "
msgstr "their stilling is true bliss. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.432, sc6
msgctxt "sn9.6:6.1"
msgid "Natthi dāni punāvāso, "
msgstr "Penelope, weaver of the web, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:6.2"
msgid "devakāyasmi jālini; "
msgstr "now there are no future lives in the hosts of gods. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:6.3"
msgid "Vikkhīṇo jātisaṃsāro, "
msgstr "Transmigration through births is finished, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.6:6.4"
msgid "natthi dāni punabbhavo”ti. "
msgstr "now there is no further existence.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
